      "timestamp": "2026-03-26T13:09:10.817+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Tim wants wsrun-2 to follow the DRC rules much more strictly, as per the PDK docs.\n\nThe only rule I can find for the pad layer is for the top metal overlap: https://gf180mcu-pdk.readthedocs.io/en/latest/physical_verification/design_manual/drm_09_1.html\nAll the other rules are guidelines: https://gf180mcu-pdk.readthedocs.io/en/latest/physical_verification/design_manual/drm_09_2.html\nHowever, as there is no mention of a minimum pad width anywhere, wafer.space has to assume a minimum width of 40x40 according to PAD.1.",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [
          {
            "id": "1423020172595298314",
            "name": "Mod",
            "color": null,
            "position": 4
